!PADS-POWERPCB-V9.5-MILS! DESIGN DATABASE ASCII FILE 1.0

*PCB*        GENERAL PARAMETERS OF THE PCB DESIGN

UNITS        0              2=Inches 1=Metric 0=Mils
MAXIMUMLAYER 2              Maximum routing layer

*REMARK*     Synthetic test for issue #23391
*REMARK*     A padstack with the same shape but different sizes on layer -2 and
*REMARK*     layer -1 must import in NORMAL mode using the primary (layer -2)
*REMARK*     size.  The imported pad must look identical regardless of whether
*REMARK*     the component is placed on the top (N) or bottom (M) of the board.
*REMARK*
*REMARK*     A padstack with different shapes on layer -2 and layer -1 (e.g.
*REMARK*     square pin-1 on top, round on bottom) still requires FRONT_INNER_BACK.

*PARTDECAL*  ITEMS

*REMARK* NAME UNITS ORIX ORIY PIECES TERMINALS STACKS TEXT LABELS
*REMARK* PAD PIN STACKLINES
*REMARK* LEVEL SIZE SHAPE [DRILL [PLATED]]

MTG_HOLE_ASYM M 0 0 0 1 1 0 0
T0 0 0 0 1
PAD 0 4
-2 200 R   100
-2 200 RT  0.000 200 50 4
-1 150 R
0  200 R

SQ_PIN1_CONN M 0 0 0 2 2 0 0
T0 0 0 0 1
T200 0 200 0 2
PAD 0 2
-2 200 R   100
-1 200 R
PAD 1 2
-2 200 S   0   100
-1 200 R

*PARTTYPE*   ITEMS

*REMARK* NAME DECALNM TYPE GATES SIGPINS UNUSEDPINNMS FLAGS ECO

MTG_HOLE_TYPE MTG_HOLE_ASYM UND 0 0 0 0 Y
SQ_PIN1_TYPE  SQ_PIN1_CONN  UND 0 0 0 0 Y

